answerText: dark matter[10] This is the adjective used to describe dark matter whose particles move slowly compared to the speed of light.

subject: Science
question: Question: Evidence for the existence of this stuff include mass discrepancies in the Coma cluster measured by Fritz Zwicky, and galaxies are surrounded by a halo of this substance. [10] Name this invisible substance that comprises approximately 26% of the universe. WIMPs are an example of it.
